list.item:
  Acute otitis media 
                                 (>6 months of age
                               ) caused by Haemophilus influenzae , Moraxella catarrhalis,  or Streptococcus pneumoniae

  Community-acquired pneumonia 
                                 (>6 months of age
                               ) due to Chlamydophila pneumoniae , Haemophilus influenzae , Mycoplasma pneumonia , or Streptococcus pneumoniae  in patients appropriate for oral therapy.

text.paragraph:
Azithromycin has been shown to be active against most isolates of the following microorganisms, both in vitro and in clinical infections. [see 
                              Indications and Usage (1)
                           ]
